<h3 style="text-indent:0;margin-left:0;margin-top:12pt;"><a name="_Toc324262275">Legal</a></h3>
<br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">In legal module user is allowed to view/ create legal and edit legal details. Legal details can be viewed in Legal accordion from Path Links by clicking on Legal Id. In Work Commitment module form Open Issues accordion, click on Create/View Legal icon for legal details. In Path Links/Furniture Links/Surface Links/Access Land Links from Issue accordion click on Create/ View Legal icon for legal details. </p>
<ol class="L3_1">
<br>
<li><h4 style="margin-top:auto;"><a name="_Toc324262276">Display Legal Details</a></h4></li></ol><br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">To view legal details from Legal accordion of Path Links, click on legal id. From Issue part of Path Links/Furniture Links/Surface Links/Access Land Links or work commitment dashboard, click on Create/View icon present on last column of Issue details. If legal is created for that issue, application opens Legal tab in left panel with detailed information in read only format with Edit button and an attachment box.</p>
<br>
<p style="text-indent:10pt;margin-left:20pt;"><img alt="" border="1" width="678" height="511" src="legal/legal_img1.png"></p>
<p style="text-indent:31pt;margin-left:185pt;"><b>Fig.1 Legal Details</b></p>
<br>
<ol class="L3_1" start="2">
<li><h4 style="margin-top:auto;"><a name="_Toc324262277">Edit Legal Details</a></h4></li></ol><br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">To edit a legal details follow the below steps;</p>
<ol class="L1_1">
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Click on Edit button, application changes attribute format to editable with Save and Cancel button.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Change the required values and click on ‘Save’ button. Application displays a message that data successfully saved and the attributes format again changed to read only format<span style="font-size:11pt;">.</span></div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">To discard changes click on ‘Cancel’ button. On clicking Cancel button application changes the attribute format to read only without saving changes.</div></li></ol>
<br>
<ol class="L3_1" start="3">
<li><h4 style="margin-top:auto;"><a name="_Toc324262278">Create Legal</a></h4></li></ol><br>
<ol class="L1_1">
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">To create legal for an issue from Issue part of work commitment dashboard or Path Links/Furniture Links/Surface Links/Access Land Links, click on Create/View Legal icon from last column of tabular list. </div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Application opens Legal tab with legal fields. </div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Enter all the field values and click on ‘Save’ button. </div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">On successful creation of the legal, application displays a message that legal has been created for selected issue. </div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Click on Cancel button to exit from Legal tab without creating a legal.</div></li></ol>
<br>
<ol class="L3_1" start="4">
<li><h4 style="margin-top:auto;"><a name="_Toc324262279">View Parent Issue</a></h4></li></ol><br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">This tool allows user to view Issue details for which the legal is created. Click on Go to Parent Issue <img alt="" border="0" width="30" height="31" src="legal/legal_img2.png"> tool in Legal tab. Application opens Issue tab with issue details of issue associated with selected legal<font face="Arial">. &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<br>
<ol class="L3_1" start="5">
<li><h4 style="margin-top:auto;"><a name="_Toc324262280">Attach/ Remove File</a></h4></li></ol><br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">This functionality allows users to add files (up to 2MB) to the selected Legal. File could be of text type, image and other type. For this application displays an attachment box with the list of already attached files. Attachment box consists of a text box ‘Description’, Browse button as File name and Attach button.</p>
<br>
<p style="margin-left:0;font-size:10pt;">To add an attachment:</p>
<ol class="L1_1">
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Enter attachment description.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Enter file path or click on Browse button to add file name from any specific location.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Click on Attach button.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">On successful attachment, attached file is displayed in Attached Files list.</div></li></ol>
<br>
<p class="No_Spacing" style="margin-left:0;font-family:'Calibri';">To remove an attachment: </p>
<ol class="L1_1">
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Click on the remove icon after the file name in Attached Files list on Legal tab.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Application displays a confirmation message to remove attachment.</div></li>
<li><div style="font-family:'Calibri';font-size:10pt">Click Ok to remove or Click Cancel to discard.</div></li></ol>
<br>
